# Phase 1 — App Domain Implementation Plan

> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.

**Goal:** Build the React + Vite SPA and its Amplify Gen 2 backend (the `Job` Data model → AppSync + DynamoDB) so a user can paste a Steam URL, watch real-time job progress via `observeQuery`, and see the nominal result — fully runnable locally with zero AWS via a local-sim.

**Architecture:** Amplify Gen 2 defines the `Job` model (the cross-domain contract, spec §3). The FE is a two-route SPA: a URL box that POSTs to the scraper's Validator Function URL, and a job view that subscribes to one `Job` row. A `JobClient` interface has two implementations — the real Amplify Data client and an in-memory `FakeAmplifyClient` — selected by an env flag, so the whole app runs offline. The Validator HTTP call is faked in tests/local by MSW.

**Tech Stack:** React 18, Vite, TypeScript, Vitest + @testing-library/react, MSW, AWS Amplify Gen 2 (`@aws-amplify/backend`, `aws-amplify`), React Router.

**Spec:** `docs/specs/2026-06-01-phase-1-design.md` (v2.1). This plan implements §3, §3.1, §5, §6 (app side), §7, §8 (app), §9 (app).

---

## File structure

```
app/
  package.json                      # deps + scripts
  tsconfig.json  tsconfig.node.json
  vite.config.ts                    # build + vitest config
  .eslintrc.cjs
  index.html
  amplify/
    backend.ts                      # defineBackend
    data/resource.ts                # Job schema (the contract)
  src/
    main.tsx                        # entry, router, Amplify.configure
    App.tsx                         # routes
    config.ts                       # env: VITE_VALIDATOR_URL, VITE_USE_FAKE
    types/job.ts                    # JobStatus, Job, JobView types (single source of truth)
    api/
      jobClient.ts                  # JobClient interface + selector
      amplifyJobClient.ts           # real impl (observeQuery wrapper)
      fakeJobClient.ts              # FakeAmplifyClient (in-memory lifecycle)
      validator.ts                  # POST to VITE_VALIDATOR_URL
    hooks/useJob.ts                 # subscribe to one Job row → JobView state machine
    routes/
      UrlBoxPage.tsx                # "/" — input + validation errors
      JobPage.tsx                   # "/job/:id" — waiting | nominal | tryagain
    components/
      WaitingScreen.tsx  NominalScreen.tsx  TryAgainScreen.tsx
    test/
      setup.ts                      # vitest + MSW + matchMedia shims
      mswHandlers.ts                # Validator HTTP mocks
  tests/                            # component/integration tests (mirrors src)
.github/workflows/app-deploy.yml    # Amplify Gen 2 pipeline + SSM publish
```

**Note on env/local:** `VITE_USE_FAKE=true` selects `fakeJobClient` and points `validator.ts` at MSW; `npm run dev` sets it. Staging builds leave it unset → real Amplify client + real `VITE_VALIDATOR_URL`.

---

## Task 1: Scaffold the app package

**Files:**
- Create: `app/package.json`, `app/tsconfig.json`, `app/tsconfig.node.json`, `app/vite.config.ts`, `app/.eslintrc.cjs`, `app/index.html`, `app/src/main.tsx`, `app/src/App.tsx`, `app/src/test/setup.ts`

